  "commentary": "With SPX at 7024.21 sitting between the max negative gamma at 7015 and max positive gamma at 7050, dealers are likely covering short hedges from the bounce off 7015 and will start selling into strength as we approach the massive 10.5B gamma wall at 7050. The PIN regime with over 103B in total GEX creates a strong mean-reversion environment, with dealers acting as stabilizers by selling rallies and buying dips around this 7015-7050 range. Watch for increased dealer selling pressure if we breach 7050, but expect strong support at the 7000 level (9.7B gamma wall) on any pullback.\n\nBottom line: expect price to get pinned between 7015-7050 with limited breakout potential.",
